text: Practice Problem 3.46 (solution page 382) Figure 3.41 shows a (low-quality) implementation of a function that reads a line from standard input, copies the string to newly allocated storage, and returns a pointer to the result. Consider the following scenario. Procedure get. line is called with the return address equal to 0x400776 and register %rbx equal to 0x0123456789ABCDEF. You type in the string 0123456789012345678901234
